hopobject.body: I'm self-employed kelavkar medical centre kolhapur The person behind the counter at my local coffee shop doesn’t care which card I’m using: he probably sees a hundred different cards every day, all of which are competing in their own way to be particularly attractive to consumers. But even if he does accept mobile payments, he’ll only accept one form of them: if he uses Square Wallet he won’t use LevelUp, or Clinkle. That’s why Clinkle got so much seed money: it’s competing in a winner-takes all space, where only one solution can win.
